properties.headline: Lake Wind Advisory issued January 4 at 8:58AM EST until January 4 at 7:00PM EST by NWS Melbourne FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds around 20 mph with higher gusts. Squall
line to push through central Florida through early evening.

* WHERE...Inland Volusia, Northern Lake, Orange, Seminole,
Southern Brevard, Osceola, Indian River, Okeechobee, St.
Lucie, Martin, Coastal Volusia, Southern Lake and Northern
Brevard Counties.

* WHEN...Until 7 PM EST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds and rough waves on area lakes will
create hazardous conditions for small craft.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A squall line approaching the I-4 corridor
at mid morning will push through central Florida through early
evening. This line will generate sustained winds around 20 mph
with higher gusts. Winds will shift to the west behind the line,
then to the northwest through sunset.
properties.instruction:
Boaters on area lakes should use extra caution since strong winds
and rough waves can overturn small craft.

NWSheadline: LAKE WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM EST THIS EVENING
